The paper deals with the problem of community search in networks, which is a topic that falls under the broad category of social and information networks (cs.SI). The paper also involves the study of graph algorithms and optimization, which are relevant to sub-categories such as cs.SD (discrete mathematics), cs.DS (data structures and algorithms), and cs.LG (machine learning). Finally, the paper proposes efficient algorithms for community search, which may be of interest to researchers in the field of control and optimization (cs.SY).
